Staying up all night watching the Olympic games can easily harm your heart
Brazil Olympic Games race is in full swing , even if the event is broadcast in the middle of the night in China , many people will stay up late to watch .
In this regard , doctors remind public that staying up late watching games might be bad for your health , raising risk of cardiovascular disease .
If you stay up all night long , a lot of this hormone will be secreted . The body will continue to be in a state of intense excitement , and cannot return to normal , which makes it easier for vasoconstriction and high blood pressure to occur ; thus resulting in cardiovascular disease .
Zhiyuan Han reminds that staying up late might cause cardiovascular disease especially for people with high blood pressure , high blood sugar , high blood lipids , smoking habits , family history and other cardiovascular risk factors .
If you stay up late , not only is your cardiovascular function affected , but also your gastrointestinal function , immune system , neuroendocrine system will be affected , and even the risk of cancer will increase .
For elder friends , Han Zhiyuan suggested them not to stay up late to watch the Olympic Games , especially those with histories of cardiovascular disease .
During the last &quot; World Cup &quot; football match , Han Zhiyuan saw a 60-year-old patient , who had an onset of myocardial infarction or it could be due to staying up late watching the game .
Han Zhiyuan introduced that , since this year , his departments have admitted some 25-year-old myocardial infarction or stroke patients , which is largely due to life style of long-term staying late .
1 . Do not stay up all night everyday , occasionally stay up all night watching favorite sports is okay , but you might want to wait until the next day to watch the event replay .
2 . Get adequate liquid supplement from time to time if you stay up all night , eating more serving of fruit can help prevent blood clots and enhance the body immunity .
