This event is seen as the peak of the cold war , known as the &quot; The Cuban missile crisis . &quot;
But little is known that during the Cold War , a powerful solar storm has nearly led the United States to the brink of nuclear war with the Soviet Union . This incident didn &apos;t open to the public until being announced by researchers for the first time on August 9 .
On May 23 , 1967 , a strong solar storm caused strong interference to the radar and radio communications of the US military in the Arctic .
These radars are part of the US Ballistic Missile Early Warning System for monitoring Soviet missiles .
This paper was written by researchers at the University of Colorado , who interviewed US military personnel involved in the forecasting and analysis of solar activity and reviewed non-confidential documents .
According to the paper , the US Air Force had kept some of their fighters which contained nuclear warheads flying in the sky in order to prevent the Soviet Union from suddenly launching a nuclear war in the 1960s .
The US military commander didn &apos;t know that the interference was made by the solar storm rather than the Soviet Union , so he ordered the fighters to get into the combat readiness state .
Fortunately , the research focusing on solar activity and its interference with the Earth launched by the US military in the late 1950s eventually prevented from the potential military conflict .
Later , he summarized the information provided by the Air Weather Service and submitted a detailed report .
The direct consequence of this solar storm is that the US military has seen space weather as a combat concern and has built a stronger space weather forecast system .
